reviews.review_text: My first show went dressed as clowns with Pat Sanley and Eric Radmaul from New Canaan CT. Got a ride home from Dave Lindsay after losing those clowns!

- A very nice first set, apart from a slightly flubby Music. 

Tape needs some EQing...but it's better than a freakin' board!?! Forget boards. They're almost never better than OK at best...well, Miller remixes and so forth excepted I suppose...

Great Scarlet/Fire. Lost/Saint is kind of a fuster cluck, with many missed changes, but at least the peak of Saint is awesomely executed. Kind of a cool Drums/Space! Other One starts off kinda aimless, but once it gets going it's fantastic, and everything from there thru Not Fade is excellent too.

Back to Back! Epic show from an epic tour! Played same (almost) dates in Spring 83/84. Coliseum just a memory now as it was demo'd a few years back.
Great ride on green gels, monster versions of Scarlet/Fire, Other One! (see also 6/27/83 for another drawn out noodley killer O.O.) NFA-everyone just going wild in the halls at that point .
Agree w/ taper, great capture/quality AUD. S/F and Other One were exceptionally well played in 83. Super special memory. Thanks again Boys!

5 degrees in December for tix This is one of the last shows that I've  "slept" out for tix... The L or the mescaline contributed to one of the most hearty and memorable nights to celebrate the coming spring GD shows.
This crew on the 5th of December... clocking in at 5 degrees, but might as well have been 72...

Still Rockin' for whatever form this energy takes!
